The following components are required for making the project
1. ESP-32 or Node MCU
2. Soil moisture sensor(resistive or capcitive)
3. Relay module
4. Oled display(i2c)
5. Breadboard
6. DHT 11 or DHT 22 temp and humidity sensor
7. Jumper wires
8. power supply 5v (can use a lm2596 regulator set at 5v) or a power bank
9. water pump(optional)

The connections to be made as per shown circuit diagram or as per set pin numbers in the code.
if changing the pins, make sure to select appropriate GPIO pins.

For IoT connectivity, one needs to download the Blynk IoT application onto their smartphone.
once done, create a project in the app, add:
  1. any form of display to monitor current sensor stats
  2. any form of light(indicator) that shows current water pump status
  3. a switch to manually control the water pump remotely.
  4. a slider to set soil moisture level to be maintained.

once done, they must be assigned appropriate vpins, and same vpins must be used in the code.
copy the header from blynk and paste it on the very top of your code to link the blynk dashboard with your code and MCU.
  
